[API Reference](#api-reference)\n    23\n    24---\n    25\n    26## Overview\n    27\n    28CommandManager is the central command processing and routing module for VOS4. It handles:\n    29\n    30- **Command Registration**: Register and manage voice command handlers\n    31- **Command Routing**: Route commands to appropriate action handlers\n    32- **Command Execution**: Execute commands with confidence-based filtering\n    33- **Macro Support**: Pre-defined and custom macro sequences\n    34- **Multi-Language**: Locale-aware command loading\n    35- **Context Awareness**: Context-sensitive command availability\n    36\n    37### Key Features\n    38\n    39-  **Direct Implementation**: Zero overhead, no unnecessary abstractions\n    40-  **Thread-Safe**: Concurrent command execution support\n    41-  **Confidence-Based**: Automatic filtering based on speech recognition confidence\n    42-  **Fuzzy Matching**: Finds best match when exact command not found\n    43-  **Extensible**: Easy to add new commands and actions\n    44-  **Type-Safe**: Strong typing throughout Kotlin codebase\n    45\n    46---\n    47\n    48## Architecture\n    49\n    50### High-Level Design\n    51\n    52```\n    53\n    54                    VoiceOSService                       \n    55                 (Accessibility Service)                 \n    56\n    57                       \n    58                       \n    59\n    60                   CommandManager                        \n    61      \n    62    Command Processing Pipeline                       \n    63    1. Receive Command                                \n    64    2. Confidence Filtering                           \n    65    3. Fuzzy Matching (if needed)                     \n    66    4. Route to Action Handler                        \n    67    5. Execute & Return Result                        \n    68      \n    69\n    70                       \n    71        \n    72                                    \n    73       \n    74   Navigation    Editing     System  \n    75    Actions      Actions    Actions  \n    76       \n    77```\n    78\n    79### Component Architecture\n    80\n    81```\n    82CommandManager\n    83 CommandRegistry         # System-wide handler registration\n    84 CommandDefinitions     # Built-in command catalog\n    85 CommandLoader          # Multi-language command loading\n    86 CommandLocalizer       # Locale management\n    87 ConfidenceScorer       # Confidence-based filtering\n    88 actions/               # Action implementations\n    89    BaseAction        # Abstract base class\n    90    NavigationActions # System navigation\n    91    EditingActions    # Text editing\n    92    CursorActions     # VoiceCursor integration\n    93    SystemActions     # System control\n    94    VolumeActions     # Audio control\n    95    MacroActions      # Macro sequences\n    96    ScrollActions     # Scrolling\n    97    GestureActions    # Gestures\n    98    ... (16 total)\n    99 models/               # Data models\n   100    Command          # Command data class\n   101    CommandResult    # Execution result\n   102    CommandContext   # Execution context\n   103    CommandDefinition # Command metadata\n   104 database/            # SQLDelight database (KMP-ready)\n   105    CommandDatabase  # Database initialization\n   106    sqldelight/      # SQLDelight adapters\n   107        VoiceCommandDaoAdapter    # Command CRUD operations\n   108        CommandUsageDaoAdapter    # Usage tracking\n   109        DatabaseVersionDaoAdapter # Version management\n   110        VoiceCommandEntity        # Command data class\n   111        TypeAliases               # Backward compatibility\n   112 routing/            # Command routing\n   113     IntentDispatcher # Intent-based routing\n   114```\n   115\n   116### Design Principles\n   117\n   1181. **Direct Implementation**: No interfaces unless strategically valuable\n   1192. **Performance First**: Optimized for low-latency command execution\n   1203. **Fail-Safe**: Always return a result, never throw exceptions to caller\n   1214. **Immutable Data**: All data models are immutable (`data class`)\n   1225. **Coroutine-Based**: All execution is suspendable for async operations\n   123\n   124### Database Architecture (SQLDelight)\n   125\n   126As of v2.0.0, CommandManager uses **SQLDelight** instead of Room for database operations. This enables Kotlin Multiplatform (KMP) compatibility.\n   127\n   128#### SQLDelight Schemas\n   129\n   130Located in: `libraries/core/database/src/commonMain/sqldelight/com/augmentalis/database/command/`\n   131\n   132| Schema | Purpose |\n   133|--------|---------|\n   134| `VoiceCommand.sq` | Voice command CRUD operations |\n   135| `CommandUsage.sq` | Command usage tracking and analytics |\n   136| `DatabaseVersion.sq` | Database version management |\n   137\n   138#### Adapter Classes\n   139\n   140CommandManager uses adapter classes to maintain backward compatibility with the previous Room-style API:\n   141\n   142```kotlin\n   143// SQLDelight adapter - wraps generated queries\n   144class VoiceCommandDaoAdapter(\n   145    private val queries: VoiceCommandQueries\n   146) {\n   147    suspend fun insert(command: VoiceCommandEntity) = withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {\n   148        queries.insertCommand(\n   149            id = command.id,\n   150            locale = command.locale,\n   151            primary_text = command.primaryText,\n   152            // ... other fields\n   153        )\n   154    }\n   155\n   156    suspend fun getCommandsForLocale(locale: String): List<VoiceCommandEntity> =\n   157        withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {\n   158            queries.getCommandsForLocale(locale).executeAsList().map { it.toEntity() }\n   159        }\n   160}\n   161```\n   162\n   163#### Migration from Room\n   164\n   165The migration preserved all existing functionality:\n   166\n   167| Room | SQLDelight Equivalent |\n   168|------|----------------------|\n   169| `@Entity` | `.sq` schema definition |\n   170| `@Dao` | `*DaoAdapter` class |\n   171| `@Query` | SQL in `.sq` file |\n   172| `Room.databaseBuilder()` | `VoiceOSDatabase()` factory |\n   173\n   174---\n   175\n   176## Core Components\n   177\n   178### 1. CommandManager\n   179\n   180**Location:** `com.augmentalis.commandmanager.CommandManager`\n   181\n   182The main entry point for command execution.\n   183\n   184#### Initialization\n   185\n   186```kotlin\n   187// Get singleton instance\n   188val commandManager = CommandManager.getInstance(context)\n   189\n   190// Initialize\n   191commandManager.initialize()\n   192```\n   193\n   194#### Command Execution\n   195\n   196```kotlin\n   197// Create command\n   198val command = Command(\n   199    id = \"nav_back\",\n   200    text = \"go back\",\n   201    source = CommandSource.VOICE,\n   202    confidence = 0.95f\n   203)\n   204\n   205// Execute with confidence filtering\n   206val result = commandManager.executeCommand(command)\n   207\n   208// Check result\n   209if (result.success) {\n   210    Log.d(TAG, \"Success: ${result.response}\")\n   211} else {\n   212    Log.e(TAG, \"Error: ${result.error?.message}\")\n   213}\n   214```\n   215\n   216#### Confidence Levels\n   217\n   218CommandManager uses four confidence levels:\n   219\n   220| Level | Range | Behavior |\n   221|-------|-------|----------|\n   222| **HIGH** | 0.85-1.00 | Execute immediately |\n   223| **MEDIUM** | 0.70-0.84 | Request confirmation (if callback set) |\n   224| **LOW** | 0.50-0.69 | Show alternatives (if callback set) |\n   225| **REJECT** | 0.00-0.49 | Reject command, return error |\n   226\n   227#### Setting Callbacks\n   228\n   229```kotlin\n   230// Confirmation callback for MEDIUM confidence\n   231commandManager.setConfirmationCallback { command, confidenceLevel ->\n   232    // Show confirmation dialog to user\n   233    // Return true to proceed, false to cancel\n   234    showConfirmationDialog(command)\n   235}\n   236\n   237// Alternatives callback for LOW confidence\n   238commandManager.setAlternativesCallback { command, alternatives ->\n   239    // Show alternatives to user\n   240    // Return selected command ID or null to cancel\n   241    showAlternativesDialog(alternatives)\n   242}\n   243```\n   244\n   245#### Multi-Language Support\n   246\n   247```kotlin\n   248// Get current locale\n   249val locale = commandManager.getCurrentLocale() // e.g., \"en-US\"\n   250\n   251// Get available locales\n   252val locales = commandManager.getAvailableLocales() // [\"en-US\", \"es-ES\", \"fr-FR\", \"de-DE\"]\n   253\n   254// Switch locale\n   255val success = commandManager.switchLocale(\"es-ES\")\n   256\n   257// Reset to system locale\n   258commandManager.resetToSystemLocale()\n   259```\n   260\n   261### 2. CommandRegistry\n   262\n   263**Location:** `com.augmentalis.commandmanager.CommandRegistry`\n   264\n   265Singleton registry for system-wide command routing.\n   266\n   267#### Registration\n   268\n   269```kotlin\n   270// Register handler for a module\n   271val handler = CursorCommandHandler()\n   272CommandRegistry.registerHandler(\"voicecursor\", handler)\n   273\n   274// Unregister handler\n   275CommandRegistry.unregisterHandler(\"voicecursor\")\n   276```\n   277\n   278#### Routing\n   279\n   280```kotlin\n   281// Route command to appropriate handler\n   282val success = CommandRegistry.routeCommand(\"cursor up\")\n   283// Returns true if handled, false if no handler found\n   284```\n   285\n   286#### Handler Discovery\n   287\n   288```kotlin\n   289// Get specific handler\n   290val handler = CommandRegistry.getHandler(\"voicecursor\")\n   291\n   292// Get all handlers\n   293val allHandlers = CommandRegistry.getAllHandlers()\n   294\n   295// Get all supported commands\n   296val commands = CommandRegistry.getAllSupportedCommands()\n   297\n   298// Check registration\n   299val isRegistered = CommandRegistry.isHandlerRegistered(\"voicecursor\")\n   300```\n   301\n   302#### Thread Safety\n   303\n   304All `CommandRegistry` operations are thread-safe:\n   305- Uses `ConcurrentHashMap` internally\n   306- Safe concurrent registration/routing\n   307- No external synchronization needed\n   308\n   309### 3. CommandDefinitions\n   310\n   311**Location:** `com.augmentalis.commandmanager.definitions.CommandDefinitions`\n   312\n   313Manages built-in command definitions.\n   314\n   315#### Usage\n   316\n   317```kotlin\n   318val definitions = CommandDefinitions()\n   319definitions.loadBuiltInCommands()\n   320\n   321// Get all definitions\n   322val allDefs = definitions.getAllDefinitions()\n   323\n   324// Get contextual commands\n   325val context = CommandContext(\n   326    packageName = \"com.android.chrome\",\n   327    viewId = \"EditText\"\n   328)\n   329val contextualDefs = definitions.getContextualCommands(context)\n   330\n   331// Add custom definition\n   332val customDef = CommandDefinition(\n   333    id = \"custom_command\",\n   334    name = \"My Custom Command\",\n   335    description = \"Does something custom\",\n   336    category = \"CUSTOM\",\n   337    patterns = listOf(\"do custom thing\", \"custom action\")\n   338)\n   339definitions.addCustomDefinition(customDef)\n   340```\n   341\n   342#### Command Categories\n   343\n   344- `NAVIGATION` - System navigation (back, home, recents)\n   345- `INPUT` - Text input and editing (type, copy, paste)\n   346- `MEDIA` - Media control (volume, mute)\n   347- `SYSTEM` - System control (WiFi, Bluetooth, settings)\n   348- `APP_CONTROL` - App management (open, close)\n   349- `ACCESSIBILITY` - Accessibility features\n   350- `CUSTOM` - User-defined commands\n   351\n   352---\n   353\n   354## Action Types\n   355\n   356CommandManager includes 16 action types:\n   357\n   358### 1. NavigationActions\n   359\n   360**Location:** `actions/NavigationActions.kt`\n   361\n   362System navigation commands.\n   363\n   364#### Available Actions\n   365\n   366| Action | Command | Description |\n   367|--------|---------|-------------|\n   368| `BackAction` | \"go back\", \"back\" | Navigate back |\n   369| `HomeAction` | \"go home\", \"home\" | Go to home screen |\n   370| `RecentAppsAction` | \"recent apps\", \"recents\" | Open recent apps |\n   371| `NotificationsAction` | \"notifications\" | Open notification panel |\n   372| `QuickSettingsAction` | \"quick settings\" | Open quick settings |\n   373| `PowerDialogAction` | \"power dialog\" | Open power menu |\n   374| `SplitScreenAction` | \"split screen\" | Toggle split screen |\n   375| `LockScreenAction` | \"lock screen\" | Lock device |\n   376| `ScreenshotAction` | \"screenshot\", \"take screenshot\" | Capture screenshot |\n   377| `AccessibilitySettingsAction` | \"accessibility settings\" | Open accessibility settings |\n   378| `DismissNotificationAction` | \"dismiss notifications\" | Close notification panel |\n   379| `AllAppsAction` | \"all apps\" | Open app drawer |\n   380\n   381#### Implementation Pattern\n   382\n   383```kotlin\n   384class BackAction : BaseAction() {\n   385    override suspend fun execute(\n   386        command: Command,\n   387        accessibilityService: AccessibilityService?,\n   388        context: Context\n   389    ): CommandResult {\n   390        return if (performGlobalAction(accessibilityService, AccessibilityService.GLOBAL_ACTION_BACK)) {\n   391            createSuccessResult(command, \"Navigated back\")\n   392        } else {\n   393            createErrorResult(command, ErrorCode.EXECUTION_FAILED, \"Failed to navigate back\")\n   394        }\n   395    }\n   396}\n   397```\n   398\n   399### 2. EditingActions\n   400\n   401**Location:** `actions/EditingActions.kt`\n   402\n   403Text editing and manipulation commands.\n   404\n   405#### Available Actions\n   406\n   407| Action | Command | Description |\n   408|--------|---------|-------------|\n   409| Copy | \"copy\" | Copy selected text to clipboard |\n   410| Paste | \"paste\" | Paste clipboard content |\n   411| Cut | \"cut\" | Cut selected text to clipboard |\n   412| Select All | \"select all\" | Select all text in focused field |\n   413| Undo | \"undo\" | Undo last edit (API 24+) |\n   414| Redo | \"redo\" | Redo last undo (API 24+) |\n   415\n   416#### Key Features\n   417\n   418- Clipboard integration\n   419- Fallback to node-level actions\n   420- Focus detection for editable fields\n   421- Android version compatibility\n   422\n   423#### Example\n   424\n   425```kotlin\n   426class EditingActions(\n   427    private val context: Context,\n   428    private val accessibilityService: AccessibilityService?\n   429) : BaseAction() {\n   430\n   431    private fun performCopy(command: Command): CommandResult {\n   432        val success = accessibilityService?.performGlobalAction(\n   433            AccessibilityNodeInfo.ACTION_COPY\n   434        ) ?: false\n   435\n   436        return if (success) {\n   437            createSuccessResult(command, \"Text copied\")\n   438        } else {\n   439            // Fallback to node-level copy\n   440            val fallbackSuccess = performNodeCopy()\n   441            if (fallbackSuccess) {\n   442                createSuccessResult(command, \"Text copied (fallback)\")\n   443            } else {\n   444                createErrorResult(command, ErrorCode.EXECUTION_FAILED, \"Copy failed\")\n   445            }\n   446        }\n   447    }\n   448}\n   449```\n   450\n   451### 3. CursorActions\n   452\n   453**Location:** `actions/CursorActions.kt`\n   454\n   455VoiceCursor integration - delegates to `VoiceCursorAPI`.\n   456\n   457#### Available Actions\n   458\n   459**Movement:**\n   460- `moveCursor(direction, distance)` - Move cursor in direction\n   461- `centerCursor()` - Center cursor on screen\n   462\n   463**Click Actions:**\n   464- `click()` - Single click\n   465- `doubleClick()` - Double click\n   466- `longPress()` - Long press\n   467\n   468**Visibility:**\n   469- `showCursor(config)` - Show cursor with config\n   470- `hideCursor()` - Hide cursor\n   471- `toggleCursor()` - Toggle visibility\n   472\n   473**Configuration:**\n   474- `showCoordinates()` - Show coordinate display\n   475- `hideCoordinates()` - Hide coordinate display\n   476- `toggleCoordinates()` - Toggle coordinate display\n   477- `setCursorType(type)` - Set cursor appearance\n   478\n   479**Scrolling:**\n   480- `scrollUp()` - Scroll up at cursor position\n   481- `scrollDown()` - Scroll down at cursor position\n   482\n   483**Advanced:**\n   484- `showMenu()` - Show cursor context menu\n   485- `openSettings(context)` - Open cursor settings\n   486- `calibrate()` - Calibrate cursor tracking (TODO)\n   487\n   488#### Example\n   489\n   490```kotlin\n   491// Move cursor\n   492val success = CursorActions.moveCursor(CursorDirection.UP, distance = 50f)\n   493\n   494// Perform click\n   495val clickSuccess = CursorActions.click()\n   496\n   497// Show cursor with custom config\n   498val config = CursorConfig(\n   499    type = CursorType.Hand,\n   500    showCoordinates = true\n   501)\n   502val showSuccess = CursorActions.showCursor(config)\n   503```\n   504\n   505### 4. SystemActions\n   506\n   507**Location:** `actions/SystemActions.kt`\n   508\n   509System control and device management.\n   510\n   511#### Available Actions\n   512\n   513**Connectivity:**\n   514- `WifiToggleAction` - Toggle WiFi\n   515- `WifiEnableAction` - Enable WiFi\n   516- `WifiDisableAction` - Disable WiFi\n   517- `BluetoothToggleAction` - Toggle Bluetooth\n   518- `BluetoothEnableAction` - Enable Bluetooth\n   519- `BluetoothDisableAction` - Disable Bluetooth\n   520\n   521**Settings:**\n   522- `OpenSettingsAction` - Open system settings (with category parameter)\n   523\n   524**Information:**\n   525- `DeviceInfoAction` - Get device information\n   526- `BatteryStatusAction` - Get battery status\n   527- `NetworkStatusAction` - Get network connection status\n   528- `StorageInfoAction` - Get storage information\n   529\n   530#### Settings Categories\n   531\n   532```kotlin\n   533// Open specific settings page\n   534val command = Command(\n   535    id = \"open_settings\",\n   536    text = \"open wifi settings\",\n   537    source = CommandSource.VOICE,\n   538    parameters = mapOf(\"category\" to \"wifi\")\n   539)\n   540```\n   541\n   542**Supported Categories:**\n   543- `wifi`, `bluetooth`, `sound`, `display`, `battery`, `storage`\n   544- `apps`, `security`, `privacy`, `accessibility`\n   545- `language`, `date`, `location`, `accounts`, `backup`\n   546- `developer`, `system`, `about`, `network`, `hotspot`, `vpn`, `nfc`\n   547\n   548### 5. val id: String,                          // Unique identifier\n   602    val name: String,                        // Display name\n   603    val description: String,                 // Human-readable description\n   604    val category: String,                    // Category (see categories above)\n   605    val patterns: List<String>,              // Voice command patterns\n   606    val parameters: List<CommandParameter> = emptyList(),  // Optional parameters\n   607    val requiredPermissions: List<String> = emptyList(),   // Required Android permissions\n   608    val supportedLanguages: List<String> = listOf(\"en\"),   // Supported languages\n   609    val requiredContext: Set<String> = emptySet()          // Required context (e.g., \"text_input\")\n   610)\n   611```\n   612\n   613### Example Definition\n   614\n   615```kotlin\n   616CommandDefinition(\n   617    id = \"cursor_click\",\n   618    name = \"Click\",\n   619    description = \"Perform click action at cursor position\",\n   620    category = \"INPUT\",\n   621    patterns = listOf(\"click\", \"tap\", \"press\", \"select\"),\n   622    parameters = listOf(\n   623        CommandParameter(\"target\", ParameterType.STRING, required = false),\n   624        CommandParameter(\"x\", ParameterType.NUMBER, required = false),\n   625        CommandParameter(\"y\", ParameterType.NUMBER, required = false)\n   626    ),\n   627    requiredPermissions = emptyList(),\n   628    supportedLanguages = listOf(\"en\", \"es\", \"fr\", \"de\"),\n   629    requiredContext = emptySet()\n   630)\n   631```\n   632\n   633### Parameter Definition\n   634\n   635```kotlin\n   636data class CommandParameter(\n   637    val name: String,              // Parameter name\n   638    val type: ParameterType,       // Parameter type\n   639    val required: Boolean = false, // Is required?\n   640    val defaultValue: Any? = null, // Default value if not provided\n   641    val description: String? = null // Parameter description\n   642)\n   643\n   644enum class ParameterType {\n   645    STRING,   // Text string\n   646    NUMBER,   // Numeric value\n   647    BOOLEAN,  // True/false\n   648    LIST,     // List of values\n   649    MAP,      // Key-value pairs\n   650    CUSTOM    // Custom type\n   651}\n   652```\n   653\n   654---\n   655\n   656## Adding New Commands\n   657\n   658### Step 1: Create Action Class\n   659\n   660Create a new action class in `actions/` directory:\n   661\n   662```kotlin\n   663// File: actions/MyCustomActions.kt\n   664package com.augmentalis.commandmanager.actions\n   665\n   666import android.accessibilityservice.AccessibilityService\n   667import android.content.Context\n   668import com.augmentalis.commandmanager.models.*\n   669\n   670class MyCustomActions : BaseAction() {\n   671\n   672    companion object {\n   673        private const val TAG = \"MyCustomActions\"\n   674    }\n   675\n   676    override suspend fun execute(\n   677        command: Command,\n   678        accessibilityService: AccessibilityService?,\n   679        context: Context\n   680    ): CommandResult {\n   681        return when (command.id) {\n   682            \"my_custom_command\" -> performCustomAction(command, context)\n   683            else -> createErrorResult(\n   684                command,\n   685                ErrorCode.UNKNOWN_COMMAND,\n   686                \"Unknown command: ${command.id}\"\n   687            )\n   688        }\n   689    }\n   690\n   691    private fun performCustomAction(\n   692        command: Command,\n   693        context: Context\n   694    ): CommandResult {\n   695        return try {\n   696            // Your custom logic here\n   697            val result = doSomethingCustom()\n   698\n   699            if (result) {\n   700                createSuccessResult(command, \"Custom action completed\")\n   701            } else {\n   702                createErrorResult(\n   703                    command,\n   704                    ErrorCode.EXECUTION_FAILED,\n   705                    \"Custom action failed\"\n   706                )\n   707            }\n   708        } catch (e: Exception) {\n   709            android.util.Log.e(TAG, \"Custom action error\", e)\n   710            createErrorResult(\n   711                command,\n   712                ErrorCode.EXECUTION_FAILED,\n   713                \"Error: ${e.message}\"\n   714            )\n   715        }\n   716    }\n   717\n   718    private fun doSomethingCustom(): Boolean {\n   719        // Your implementation\n   720        return true\n   721    }\n   722}\n   723```\n   724\n   725### Step 2: Add Command Definition\n   726\n   727Add to `CommandDefinitions.kt`:\n   728\n   729```kotlin\n   730private fun loadCustomCommands() {\n   731    builtInDefinitions[\"my_custom_command\"] = CommandDefinition(\n   732        id = \"my_custom_command\",\n   733        name = \"My Custom Command\",\n   734        description = \"Does something custom\",\n   735        category = \"CUSTOM\",\n   736        patterns = listOf(\"do custom thing\", \"custom action\", \"my command\"),\n   737        parameters = listOf(\n   738            CommandParameter(\"param1\", ParameterType.STRING, required = false)\n   739        )\n   740    )\n   741}\n   742```\n   743\n   744### Step 3: Register in CommandManager\n   745\n   746Add to `CommandManager.kt` initialization:\n   747\n   748```kotlin\n   749private val customActions = mapOf(\n   750    \"my_custom_command\" to MyCustomActions()\n   751)\n   752\n   753private suspend fun executeCommandInternal(command: Command): CommandResult {\n   754    var action = when {\n   755        // ... existing mappings ...\n   756        command.id == \"my_custom_command\" -> customActions[command.id]\n   757        else -> null\n   758    }\n   759\n   760    // ... rest of execution logic ...\n   761}\n   762```\n   763\n   764### Step 4: Add Tests\n   765\n   766Create test file `actions/MyCustomActionsTest.kt`:\n   767\n   768```kotlin\n   769@RunWith(AndroidJUnit4::class)\n   770class MyCustomActionsTest {\n   771\n   772    private lateinit var actions: MyCustomActions\n   773    private lateinit var context: Context\n   774\n   775    @Before\n   776    fun setUp() {\n   777        context = InstrumentationRegistry.getInstrumentation().targetContext\n   778        actions = MyCustomActions()\n   779    }\n   780\n   781    @Test\n   782    fun testCustomAction() = runTest {\n   783        val command = Command(\n   784            id = \"my_custom_command\",\n   785            text = \"do custom thing\",\n   786            source = CommandSource.VOICE\n   787        )\n   788\n   789        val result = actions.execute(command, null, context)\n   790\n   791        assertTrue(result.success)\n   792        assertEquals(\"Custom action completed\", result.response)\n   793    }\n   794}\n   795```\n   796\n   797### Step 5: Document\n   798\n   7991. Add to this manual under [Action Types](#action-types)\n   8002. Add to user manual with user-friendly description\n   8013. Update changelog\n   802\n   803---\n   804\n   805## Macro System\n   806\n   807Macros allow sequential execution of multiple commands.\n   808\n   809### Pre-Defined Macros\n   810\n   811**Location:** `actions/MacroActions.kt`\n   812\n   813#### Available Macros\n   814\n   815| Macro | Steps | Category | Description |\n   816|-------|-------|----------|-------------|\n   817| **Select All and Copy** | `[\"select all\", \"copy\"]` | EDITING | Select all text and copy to clipboard |\n   818| **Select All and Cut** | `[\"select all\", \"cut\"]` | EDITING | Select all text and cut to clipboard |\n   819| **Paste and Enter** | `[\"paste\", \"press enter\"]` | EDITING | Paste content and press Enter |\n   820| **Screenshot and Share** | `[\"screenshot\", \"share\"]` | PRODUCTIVITY | Take screenshot and open share dialog |\n   821\n   822### Macro Structure\n   823\n   824```kotlin\n   825data class Macro(\n   826    val name: String,\n   827    val steps: List<String>,\n   828    val category: MacroCategory,\n   829    val description: String,\n   830    val parameters: List<MacroParameter> = emptyList()\n   831)\n   832\n   833enum class MacroCategory {\n   834    EDITING,        // Text/content editing workflows\n   835    NAVIGATION,     // App/screen navigation workflows\n   836    ACCESSIBILITY,  // Accessibility-focused workflows\n   837    PRODUCTIVITY    // General productivity workflows\n   838}\n   839```\n   840\n   841### Macro Variables\n   842\n   843Macros support parameterized steps:\n   844\n   845```kotlin\n   846data class MacroParameter(\n   847    val name: String,\n   848    val type: MacroParameterType,\n   849    val description: String,\n   850    val defaultValue: String? = null,\n   851    val required: Boolean = false\n   852)\n   853\n   854enum class MacroParameterType {\n   855    APP,      // Application name/package\n   856    TEXT,     // Text string\n   857    NUMBER    // Numeric value\n   858}\n   859```\n   860\n   861**Example with Variables:**\n   862\n   863```kotlin\n   864Macro(\n   865    name = \"Open App and Navigate\",\n   866    steps = listOf(\n   867        \"open [app]\",\n   868        \"wait 500\",\n   869        \"navigate to [section]\"\n   870    ),\n   871    category = MacroCategory.NAVIGATION,\n   872    description = \"Open app and navigate to section\",\n   873    parameters = listOf(\n   874        MacroParameter(\"app\", MacroParameterType.APP, \"App to open\", required = true),\n   875        MacroParameter(\"section\", MacroParameterType.TEXT, \"Section to navigate to\")\n   876    )\n   877)\n   878```\n   879\n   880### Executing Macros\n   881\n   882```kotlin\n   883val macroActions = MacroActions(commandExecutor)\n   884\n   885val command = Command(\n   886    id = \"macro\",\n   887    text = \"select all and copy\",\n   888    source = CommandSource.VOICE,\n   889    parameters = mapOf() // Variables go here\n   890)\n   891\n   892val result = macroActions.execute(command, accessibilityService, context)\n   893\n   894// Check result\n   895if (result.success) {\n   896    val data = result.data as MacroExecutionData\n   897    println(\"Completed ${data.completedSteps}/${data.totalSteps} steps\")\n   898}\n   899```\n   900\n   901### Macro Execution Data\n   902\n   903```kotlin\n   904data class MacroExecutionData(\n   905    val macroName: String,\n   906    val totalSteps: Int,\n   907    val completedSteps: Int,\n   908    val stepResults: List<StepResult>,\n   909    val executionTimeMs: Long = 0\n   910)\n   911\n   912data class StepResult(\n   913    val stepNumber: Int,\n   914    val stepText: String,\n   915    val success: Boolean,\n   916    val error: String? = null\n   917)\n   918```\n   919\n   920### Creating Custom Macros (Future)\n   921\n   922Currently stubbed for V2. Will support:\n   923- User-created macros\n   924- Macro sharing (export/import)\n   925- Conditional logic (if/then/else)\n   926- Loop support\n   927- Macro marketplace\n   928\n   929---\n   930\n   931## Multi-Language Support\n   932\n   933CommandManager supports multiple languages through a locale-aware system.\n   934\n   935### Supported Locales\n   936\n   937- `en-US` - English (United States)\n   938- `es-ES` - Spanish (Spain)\n   939- `fr-FR` - French (France)\n   940- `de-DE` - German (Germany)\n   941\n   942### Command Files\n   943\n   944Located in: `src/main/assets/commands/`\n   945\n   946```\n   947commands/\n   948 en-US/\n   949    navigation.json\n   950    editing.json\n   951    system.json\n   952 es-ES/\n   953    navigation.json\n   954    ...\n   955 ...\n   956```\n   957\n   958### JSON Format\n   959\n   960```json\n   961{\n   962  \"locale\": \"en-US\",\n   963  \"commands\": [\n   964    {\n   965      \"id\": \"nav_back\",\n   966      \"patterns\": [\"go back\", \"back\", \"navigate back\", \"previous\", \"return\"],\n   967      \"category\": \"NAVIGATION\",\n   968      \"description\": \"Navigate back to previous screen\"\n   969    },\n   970    {\n   971      \"id\": \"nav_home\",\n   972      \"patterns\": [\"go home\", \"home\", \"home screen\", \"main screen\"],\n   973      \"category\": \"NAVIGATION\",\n   974      \"description\": \"Go to home screen\"\n   975    }\n   976  ]\n   977}\n   978```\n   979\n   980### Adding New Locale\n   981\n   9821. **Create locale directory** in `assets/commands/` (e.g., `ja-JP/`)\n   983\n   9842. **Create command JSON files** for each category\n   985\n   9863. **Translate command patterns** to target language\n   987\n   9884. **Test locale loading:**\n   989\n   990```kotlin\n   991val commandManager = CommandManager.getInstance(context)\n   992val success = commandManager.switchLocale(\"ja-JP\")\n   993```\n   994\n   995### Locale Fallback\n   996\n   997If requested locale not found:\n   9981. Try language-only match (e.g., `en-US`  `en`)\n   9992. Fall back to English (`en-US`)\n  10003. [Overview](#overview)\n2. [Architecture](#architecture)\n3. [Core Components](#core-components)\n4. [Action Types](#action-types)\n5. [Command Definition Format](#command-definition-format)\n6. [Adding New Commands](#adding-new-commands)\n7. [Macro System](#macro-system)\n8. [Multi-Language Support](#multi-language-support)\n9. [Testing](#testing)\n10. [API Reference](#api-reference)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nCommandManager is the central command processing and routing module for VOS4. It handles:\n\n- **Command Registration**: Register and manage voice command handlers\n- **Command Routing**: Route commands to appropriate action handlers\n- **Command Execution**: Execute commands with confidence-based filtering\n- **Macro Support**: Pre-defined and custom macro sequences\n- **Multi-Language**: Locale-aware command loading\n- **Context Awareness**: Context-sensitive command availability\n\n### Key Features\n\n-  **Direct Implementation**: Zero overhead, no unnecessary abstractions\n-  **Thread-Safe**: Concurrent command execution support\n-  **Confidence-Based**: Automatic filtering based on speech recognition confidence\n-  **Fuzzy Matching**: Finds best match when exact command not found\n-  **Extensible**: Easy to add new commands and actions\n-  **Type-Safe**: Strong typing throughout Kotlin codebase\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n\n                    VoiceOSService                       \n                 (Accessibility Service)                 \n\n                       \n                       \n\n                   CommandManager                        \n      \n    Command Processing Pipeline                       \n    1. Receive Command                                \n    2. Confidence Filtering                           \n    3. Fuzzy Matching (if needed)                     \n    4. Route to Action Handler                        \n    5. Execute & Return Result                        \n      \n\n                       \n        \n                                    \n       \n   Navigation    Editing     System  \n    Actions      Actions    Actions  \n       \n```\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n```\nCommandManager\n CommandRegistry         # System-wide handler registration\n CommandDefinitions     # Built-in command catalog\n CommandLoader          # Multi-language command loading\n CommandLocalizer       # Locale management\n ConfidenceScorer       # Confidence-based filtering\n actions/               # Action implementations\n    BaseAction        # Abstract base class\n    NavigationActions # System navigation\n    EditingActions    # Text editing\n    CursorActions     # VoiceCursor integration\n    SystemActions     # System control\n    VolumeActions     # Audio control\n    MacroActions      # Macro sequences\n    ScrollActions     # Scrolling\n    GestureActions    # Gestures\n    ... (16 total)\n models/               # Data models\n    Command          # Command data class\n    CommandResult    # Execution result\n    CommandContext   # Execution context\n    CommandDefinition # Command metadata\n database/            # SQLDelight database (KMP-ready)\n    CommandDatabase  # Database initialization\n    sqldelight/      # SQLDelight adapters\n        VoiceCommandDaoAdapter    # Command CRUD operations\n        CommandUsageDaoAdapter    # Usage tracking\n        DatabaseVersionDaoAdapter # Version management\n        VoiceCommandEntity        # Command data class\n        TypeAliases               # Backward compatibility\n routing/            # Command routing\n     IntentDispatcher # Intent-based routing\n```\n\n### Design Principles\n\n1. **Direct Implementation**: No interfaces unless strategically valuable\n2. **Performance First**: Optimized for low-latency command execution\n3. **Fail-Safe**: Always return a result, never throw exceptions to caller\n4. **Immutable Data**: All data models are immutable (`data class`)\n5. **Coroutine-Based**: All execution is suspendable for async operations\n\n### Database Architecture (SQLDelight)\n\nAs of v2.0.0, CommandManager uses **SQLDelight** instead of Room for database operations. This enables Kotlin Multiplatform (KMP) compatibility.\n\n#### SQLDelight Schemas\n\nLocated in: `libraries/core/database/src/commonMain/sqldelight/com/augmentalis/database/command/`\n\n| Schema | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `VoiceCommand.sq` | Voice command CRUD operations |\n| `CommandUsage.sq` | Command usage tracking and analytics |\n| `DatabaseVersion.sq` | Database version management |\n\n#### Adapter Classes\n\nCommandManager uses adapter classes to maintain backward compatibility with the previous Room-style API:\n\n```kotlin\n// SQLDelight adapter - wraps generated queries\nclass VoiceCommandDaoAdapter(\n    private val queries: VoiceCommandQueries\n) {\n    suspend fun insert(command: VoiceCommandEntity) = withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {\n        queries.insertCommand(\n            id = command.id,\n            locale = command.locale,\n            primary_text = command.primaryText,\n            // ... other fields\n        )\n    }\n\n    suspend fun getCommandsForLocale(locale: String): List<VoiceCommandEntity> =\n        withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {\n            queries.getCommandsForLocale(locale).executeAsList().map { it.toEntity() }\n        }\n}\n```\n\n#### Migration from Room\n\nThe migration preserved all existing functionality:\n\n| Room | SQLDelight Equivalent |\n|------|----------------------|\n| `@Entity` | `.sq` schema definition |\n| `@Dao` | `*DaoAdapter` class |\n| `@Query` | SQL in `.sq` file |\n| `Room.databaseBuilder()` | `VoiceOSDatabase()` factory |\n\n---\n\n## Core Components\n\n### 1. CommandManager\n\n**Location:** `com.augmentalis.commandmanager.CommandManager`\n\nThe main entry point for command execution.\n\n#### Initialization\n\n```kotlin\n// Get singleton instance\nval commandManager = CommandManager.getInstance(context)\n\n// Initialize\ncommandManager.initialize()\n```\n\n#### Command Execution\n\n```kotlin\n// Create command\nval command = Command(\n    id = \"nav_back\",\n    text = \"go back\",\n    source = CommandSource.VOICE,\n    confidence = 0.95f\n)\n\n// Execute with confidence filtering\nval result = commandManager.executeCommand(command)\n\n// Check result\nif (result.success) {\n    Log.d(TAG, \"Success: ${result.response}\")\n} else {\n    Log.e(TAG, \"Error: ${result.error?.message}\")\n}\n```\n\n#### Confidence Levels\n\nCommandManager uses four confidence levels:\n\n| Level | Range | Behavior |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| **HIGH** | 0.85-1.00 | Execute immediately |\n| **MEDIUM** | 0.70-0.84 | Request confirmation (if callback set) |\n| **LOW** | 0.50-0.69 | Show alternatives (if callback set) |\n| **REJECT** | 0.00-0.49 | Reject command, return error |\n\n#### Setting Callbacks\n\n```kotlin\n// Confirmation callback for MEDIUM confidence\ncommandManager.setConfirmationCallback { command, confidenceLevel ->\n    // Show confirmation dialog to user\n    // Return true to proceed, false to cancel\n    showConfirmationDialog(command)\n}\n\n// Alternatives callback for LOW confidence\ncommandManager.setAlternativesCallback { command, alternatives ->\n    // Show alternatives to user\n    // Return selected command ID or null to cancel\n    showAlternativesDialog(alternatives)\n}\n```\n\n#### Multi-Language Support\n\n```kotlin\n// Get current locale\nval locale = commandManager.getCurrentLocale() // e.g., \"en-US\"\n\n// Get available locales\nval locales = commandManager.getAvailableLocales() // [\"en-US\", \"es-ES\", \"fr-FR\", \"de-DE\"]\n\n// Switch locale\nval success = commandManager.switchLocale(\"es-ES\")\n\n// Reset to system locale\ncommandManager.resetToSystemLocale()\n```\n\n### 2. CommandRegistry\n\n**Location:** `com.augmentalis.commandmanager.CommandRegistry`\n\nSingleton registry for system-wide command routing.\n\n#### Registration\n\n```kotlin\n// Register handler for a module\nval handler = CursorCommandHandler()\nCommandRegistry.registerHandler(\"voicecursor\", handler)\n\n// Unregister handler\nCommandRegistry.unregisterHandler(\"voicecursor\")\n```\n\n#### Routing\n\n```kotlin\n// Route command to appropriate handler\nval success = CommandRegistry.routeCommand(\"cursor up\")\n// Returns true if handled, false if no handler found\n```\n\n#### Handler Discovery\n\n```kotlin\n// Get specific handler\nval handler = CommandRegistry.getHandler(\"voicecursor\")\n\n// Get all handlers\nval allHandlers = CommandRegistry.getAllHandlers()\n\n// Get all supported commands\nval commands = CommandRegistry.getAllSupportedCommands()\n\n// Check registration\nval isRegistered = CommandRegistry.isHandlerRegistered(\"voicecursor\")\n```\n\n#### Thread Safety\n\nAll `CommandRegistry` operations are thread-safe:\n- Uses `ConcurrentHashMap` internally\n- Safe concurrent registration/routing\n- No external synchronization needed\n\n### 3. CommandDefinitions\n\n**Location:** `com.augmentalis.commandmanager.definitions.CommandDefinitions`\n\nManages built-in command definitions.\n\n#### Usage\n\n```kotlin\nval definitions = CommandDefinitions()\ndefinitions.loadBuiltInCommands()\n\n// Get all definitions\nval allDefs = definitions.getAllDefinitions()\n\n// Get contextual commands\nval context = CommandContext(\n    packageName = \"com.android.chrome\",\n    viewId = \"EditText\"\n)\nval contextualDefs = definitions.getContextualCommands(context)\n\n// Add custom definition\nval customDef = CommandDefinition(\n    id = \"custom_command\",\n    name = \"My Custom Command\",\n    description = \"Does something custom\",\n    category = \"CUSTOM\",\n    patterns = listOf(\"do custom thing\", \"custom action\")\n)\ndefinitions.addCustomDefinition(customDef)\n```\n\n#### Command Categories\n\n- `NAVIGATION` - System navigation (back, home, recents)\n- `INPUT` - Text input and editing (type, copy, paste)\n- `MEDIA` - Media control (volume, mute)\n- `SYSTEM` - System control (WiFi, Bluetooth, settings)\n- `APP_CONTROL` - App management (open, close)\n- `ACCESSIBILITY` - Accessibility features\n- `CUSTOM` - User-defined commands\n\n---\n\n## Action Types\n\nCommandManager includes 16 action types:\n\n### 1. NavigationActions\n\n**Location:** `actions/NavigationActions.kt`\n\nSystem navigation commands.\n\n#### Available Actions\n\n| Action | Command | Description |\n|--------|---------|-------------|\n| `BackAction` | \"go back\", \"back\" | Navigate back |\n| `HomeAction` | \"go home\", \"home\" | Go to home screen |\n| `RecentAppsAction` | \"recent apps\", \"recents\" | Open recent apps |\n| `NotificationsAction` | \"notifications\" | Open notification panel |\n| `QuickSettingsAction` | \"quick settings\" | Open quick settings |\n| `PowerDialogAction` | \"power dialog\" | Open power menu |\n| `SplitScreenAction` | \"split screen\" | Toggle split screen |\n| `LockScreenAction` | \"lock screen\" | Lock device |\n| `ScreenshotAction` | \"screenshot\", \"take screenshot\" | Capture screenshot |\n| `AccessibilitySettingsAction` | \"accessibility settings\" | Open accessibility settings |\n| `DismissNotificationAction` | \"dismiss notifications\" | Close notification panel |\n| `AllAppsAction` | \"all apps\" | Open app drawer |\n\n#### Implementation Pattern\n\n```kotlin\nclass BackAction : BaseAction() {\n    override suspend fun execute(\n        command: Command,\n        accessibilityService: AccessibilityService?,\n        context: Context\n    ): CommandResult {\n        return if (performGlobalAction(accessibilityService, AccessibilityService.GLOBAL_ACTION_BACK)) {\n            createSuccessResult(command, \"Navigated back\")\n        } else {\n            createErrorResult(command, ErrorCode.EXECUTION_FAILED, \"Failed to navigate back\")\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 2. EditingActions\n\n**Location:** `actions/EditingActions.kt`\n\nText editing and manipulation commands.\n\n#### Available Actions\n\n| Action | Command | Description |\n|--------|---------|-------------|\n| Copy | \"copy\" | Copy selected text to clipboard |\n| Paste | \"paste\" | Paste clipboard content |\n| Cut | \"cut\" | Cut selected text to clipboard |\n| Select All | \"select all\" | Select all text in focused field |\n| Undo | \"undo\" | Undo last edit (API 24+) |\n| Redo | \"redo\" | Redo last undo (API 24+) |\n\n#### Key Features\n\n- Clipboard integration\n- Fallback to node-level actions\n- Focus detection for editable fields\n- Android version compatibility\n\n#### Example\n\n```kotlin\nclass EditingActions(\n    private val context: Context,\n    private val accessibilityService: AccessibilityService?\n) : BaseAction() {\n\n    private fun performCopy(command: Command): CommandResult {\n        val success = accessibilityService?.performGlobalAction(\n            AccessibilityNodeInfo.ACTION_COPY\n        ) ?: false\n\n        return if (success) {\n            createSuccessResult(command, \"Text copied\")\n        } else {\n            // Fallback to node-level copy\n            val fallbackSuccess = performNodeCopy()\n            if (fallbackSuccess) {\n                createSuccessResult(command, \"Text copied (fallback)\")\n            } else {\n                createErrorResult(command, ErrorCode.EXECUTION_FAILED, \"Copy failed\")\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3. CursorActions\n\n**Location:** `actions/CursorActions.kt`\n\nVoiceCursor integration - delegates to `VoiceCursorAPI`.\n\n#### Available Actions\n\n**Movement:**\n- `moveCursor(direction, distance)` - Move cursor in direction\n- `centerCursor()` - Center cursor on screen\n\n**Click Actions:**\n- `click()` - Single click\n- `doubleClick()` - Double click\n- `longPress()` - Long press\n\n**Visibility:**\n- `showCursor(config)` - Show cursor with config\n- `hideCursor()` - Hide cursor\n- `toggleCursor()` - Toggle visibility\n\n**Configuration:**\n- `showCoordinates()` - Show coordinate display\n- `hideCoordinates()` - Hide coordinate display\n- `toggleCoordinates()` - Toggle coordinate display\n- `setCursorType(type)` - Set cursor appearance\n\n**Scrolling:**\n- `scrollUp()` - Scroll up at cursor position\n- `scrollDown()` - Scroll down at cursor position\n\n**Advanced:**\n- `showMenu()` - Show cursor context menu\n- `openSettings(context)` - Open cursor settings\n- `calibrate()` - Calibrate cursor tracking (TODO)\n\n#### Example\n\n```kotlin\n// Move cursor\nval success = CursorActions.moveCursor(CursorDirection.UP, distance = 50f)\n\n// Perform click\nval clickSuccess = CursorActions.click()\n\n// Show cursor with custom config\nval config = CursorConfig(\n    type = CursorType.Hand,\n    showCoordinates = true\n)\nval showSuccess = CursorActions.showCursor(config)\n```\n\n### 4. SystemActions\n\n**Location:** `actions/SystemActions.kt`\n\nSystem control and device management.\n\n#### Available Actions\n\n**Connectivity:**\n- `WifiToggleAction` - Toggle WiFi\n- `WifiEnableAction` - Enable WiFi\n- `WifiDisableAction` - Disable WiFi\n- `BluetoothToggleAction` - Toggle Bluetooth\n- `BluetoothEnableAction` - Enable Bluetooth\n- `BluetoothDisableAction` - Disable Bluetooth\n\n**Settings:**\n- `OpenSettingsAction` - Open system settings (with category parameter)\n\n**Information:**\n- `DeviceInfoAction` - Get device information\n- `BatteryStatusAction` - Get battery status\n- `NetworkStatusAction` - Get network connection status\n- `StorageInfoAction` - Get storage information\n\n#### Settings Categories\n\n```kotlin\n// Open specific settings page\nval command = Command(\n    id = \"open_settings\",\n    text = \"open wifi settings\",\n    source = CommandSource.VOICE,\n    parameters = mapOf(\"category\" to \"wifi\")\n)\n```\n\n**Supported Categories:**\n- `wifi`, `bluetooth`, `sound`, `display`, `battery`, `storage`\n- `apps`, `security`, `privacy`, `accessibility`\n- `language`, `date`, `location`, `accounts`, `backup`\n- `developer`, `system`, `about`, `network`, `hotspot`, `vpn`, `nfc`\n\n### 5. VolumeActions\n\n**Location:** `actions/VolumeActions.kt`\n\nAudio volume control.\n\n#### Available Actions\n\n| Action | Parameters | Description |\n|--------|------------|-------------|\n| Volume Up | `steps` (optional), `stream` (optional) | Increase volume |\n| Volume Down | `steps` (optional), `stream` (optional) | Decrease volume |\n| Mute | `stream` (optional) | Mute audio stream |\n| Unmute | `stream` (optional) | Unmute audio stream |\n\n**Audio Streams:**\n- `MUSIC` - Media playback\n- `RING` - Ringtone\n- `NOTIFICATION` - Notifications\n- `ALARM` - Alarms\n- `SYSTEM` - System sounds\n- `VOICE_CALL` - Phone calls\n\n### 6. MacroActions\n\n**Location:** `actions/MacroActions.kt`\n\nPre-defined macro sequences.\n\n**See [Macro System](#macro-system) section for details.**\n\n### 7-16. Other Action Types\n\n**ScrollActions:** Scrolling commands (up, down, left, right)\n**GestureActions:** Gesture commands (swipe, pinch, rotate)\n**DragActions:** Drag and drop operations\n**DictationActions:** Dictation mode control\n**TextActions:** Text manipulation (insert, replace, format)\n**AppActions:** Application control (launch, switch, close)\n**NotificationActions:** Notification management\n**OverlayActions:** Overlay control (HUD, popups)\n**ShortcutActions:** Custom shortcuts\n\n---\n\n## Command Definition Format\n\nCommands are defined using the `CommandDefinition` data class.\n\n### Structure\n\n```kotlin\ndata class CommandDefinition(\n    val id: String,                          // Unique identifier\n    val name: String,                        // Display name\n    val description: String,                 // Human-readable description\n    val category: String,                    // Category (see categories above)\n    val patterns: List<String>,              // Voice command patterns\n    val parameters: List<CommandParameter> = emptyList(),  // Optional parameters\n    val requiredPermissions: List<String> = emptyList(),   // Required Android permissions\n    val supportedLanguages: List<String> = listOf(\"en\"),   // Supported languages\n    val requiredContext: Set<String> = emptySet()          // Required context (e.g., \"text_input\")\n)\n```\n\n### Example Definition\n\n```kotlin\nCommandDefinition(\n    id = \"cursor_click\",\n    name = \"Click\",\n    description = \"Perform click action at cursor position\",\n    category = \"INPUT\",\n    patterns = listOf(\"click\", \"tap\", \"press\", \"select\"),\n    parameters = listOf(\n        CommandParameter(\"target\", ParameterType.STRING, required = false),\n        CommandParameter(\"x\", ParameterType.NUMBER, required = false),\n        CommandParameter(\"y\", ParameterType.NUMBER, required = false)\n    ),\n    requiredPermissions = emptyList(),\n    supportedLanguages = listOf(\"en\", \"es\", \"fr\", \"de\"),\n    requiredContext = emptySet()\n)\n```\n\n### Parameter Definition\n\n```kotlin\ndata class CommandParameter(\n    val name: String,              // Parameter name\n    val type: ParameterType,       // Parameter type\n    val required: Boolean = false, // Is required?\n    val defaultValue: Any? = null, // Default value if not provided\n    val description: String? = null // Parameter description\n)\n\nenum class ParameterType {\n    STRING,   // Text string\n    NUMBER,   // Numeric value\n    BOOLEAN,  // True/false\n    LIST,     // List of values\n    MAP,      // Key-value pairs\n    CUSTOM    // Custom type\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Adding New Commands\n\n### Step 1: Create Action Class\n\nCreate a new action class in `actions/` directory:\n\n```kotlin\n// File: actions/MyCustomActions.kt\npackage com.augmentalis.commandmanager.actions\n\nimport android.accessibilityservice.AccessibilityService\nimport android.content.Context\nimport com.augmentalis.commandmanager.models.*\n\nclass MyCustomActions : BaseAction() {\n\n    companion object {\n        private const val TAG = \"MyCustomActions\"\n    }\n\n    override suspend fun execute(\n        command: Command,\n        accessibilityService: AccessibilityService?,\n        context: Context\n    ): CommandResult {\n        return when (command.id) {\n            \"my_custom_command\" -> performCustomAction(command, context)\n            else -> createErrorResult(\n                command,\n                ErrorCode.UNKNOWN_COMMAND,\n                \"Unknown command: ${command.id}\"\n            )\n        }\n    }\n\n    private fun performCustomAction(\n        command: Command,\n        context: Context\n    ): CommandResult {\n        return try {\n            // Your custom logic here\n            val result = doSomethingCustom()\n\n            if (result) {\n                createSuccessResult(command, \"Custom action completed\")\n            } else {\n                createErrorResult(\n                    command,\n                    ErrorCode.EXECUTION_FAILED,\n                    \"Custom action failed\"\n                )\n            }\n        } catch (e: Exception) {\n            android.util.Log.e(TAG, \"Custom action error\", e)\n            createErrorResult(\n                command,\n                ErrorCode.EXECUTION_FAILED,\n                \"Error: ${e.message}\"\n            )\n        }\n    }\n\n    private fun doSomethingCustom(): Boolean {\n        // Your implementation\n        return true\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Step 2: Add Command Definition\n\nAdd to `CommandDefinitions.kt`:\n\n```kotlin\nprivate fun loadCustomCommands() {\n    builtInDefinitions[\"my_custom_command\"] = CommandDefinition(\n        id = \"my_custom_command\",\n        name = \"My Custom Command\",\n        description = \"Does something custom\",\n        category = \"CUSTOM\",\n        patterns = listOf(\"do custom thing\", \"custom action\", \"my command\"),\n        parameters = listOf(\n            CommandParameter(\"param1\", ParameterType.STRING, required = false)\n        )\n    )\n}\n```\n\n### Step 3: Register in CommandManager\n\nAdd to `CommandManager.kt` initialization:\n\n```kotlin\nprivate val customActions = mapOf(\n    \"my_custom_command\" to MyCustomActions()\n)\n\nprivate suspend fun executeCommandInternal(command: Command): CommandResult {\n    var action = when {\n        // ... existing mappings ...\n        command.id == \"my_custom_command\" -> customActions[command.id]\n        else -> null\n    }\n\n    // ... rest of execution logic ...\n}\n```\n\n### Step 4: Add Tests\n\nCreate test file `actions/MyCustomActionsTest.kt`:\n\n```kotlin\n@RunWith(AndroidJUnit4::class)\nclass MyCustomActionsTest {\n\n    private lateinit var actions: MyCustomActions\n    private lateinit var context: Context\n\n    @Before\n    fun setUp() {\n        context = InstrumentationRegistry.getInstrumentation().targetContext\n        actions = MyCustomActions()\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun testCustomAction() = runTest {\n        val command = Command(\n            id = \"my_custom_command\",\n            text = \"do custom thing\",\n            source = CommandSource.VOICE\n        )\n\n        val result = actions.execute(command, null, context)\n\n        assertTrue(result.success)\n        assertEquals(\"Custom action completed\", result.response)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Step 5: Document\n\n1. Add to this manual under [Action Types](#action-types)\n2. Add to user manual with user-friendly description\n3. Update changelog\n\n---\n\n## Macro System\n\nMacros allow sequential execution of multiple commands.\n\n### Pre-Defined Macros\n\n**Location:** `actions/MacroActions.kt`\n\n#### Available Macros\n\n| Macro | Steps | Category | Description |\n|-------|-------|----------|-------------|\n| **Select All and Copy** | `[\"select all\", \"copy\"]` | EDITING | Select all text and copy to clipboard |\n| **Select All and Cut** | `[\"select all\", \"cut\"]` | EDITING | Select all text and cut to clipboard |\n| **Paste and Enter** | `[\"paste\", \"press enter\"]` | EDITING | Paste content and press Enter |\n| **Screenshot and Share** | `[\"screenshot\", \"share\"]` | PRODUCTIVITY | Take screenshot and open share dialog |\n\n### Macro Structure\n\n```kotlin\ndata class Macro(\n    val name: String,\n    val steps: List<String>,\n    val category: MacroCategory,\n    val description: String,\n    val parameters: List<MacroParameter> = emptyList()\n)\n\nenum class MacroCategory {\n    EDITING,        // Text/content editing workflows\n    NAVIGATION,     // App/screen navigation workflows\n    ACCESSIBILITY,  // Accessibility-focused workflows\n    PRODUCTIVITY    // General productivity workflows\n}\n```\n\n### Macro Variables\n\nMacros support parameterized steps:\n\n```kotlin\ndata class MacroParameter(\n    val name: String,\n    val type: MacroParameterType,\n    val description: String,\n    val defaultValue: String? = null,\n    val required: Boolean = false\n)\n\nenum class MacroParameterType {\n    APP,      // Application name/package\n    TEXT,     // Text string\n    NUMBER    // Numeric value\n}\n```\n\n**Example with Variables:**\n\n```kotlin\nMacro(\n    name = \"Open App and Navigate\",\n    steps = listOf(\n        \"open [app]\",\n        \"wait 500\",\n        \"navigate to [section]\"\n    ),\n    category = MacroCategory.NAVIGATION,\n    description = \"Open app and navigate to section\",\n    parameters = listOf(\n        MacroParameter(\"app\", MacroParameterType.APP, \"App to open\", required = true),\n        MacroParameter(\"section\", MacroParameterType.TEXT, \"Section to navigate to\")\n    )\n)\n```\n\n### Executing Macros\n\n```kotlin\nval macroActions = MacroActions(commandExecutor)\n\nval command = Command(\n    id = \"macro\",\n    text = \"select all and copy\",\n    source = CommandSource.VOICE,\n    parameters = mapOf() // Variables go here\n)\n\nval result = macroActions.execute(command, accessibilityService, context)\n\n// Check result\nif (result.success) {\n    val data = result.data as MacroExecutionData\n    println(\"Completed ${data.completedSteps}/${data.totalSteps} steps\")\n}\n```\n\n### Macro Execution Data\n\n```kotlin\ndata class MacroExecutionData(\n    val macroName: String,\n    val totalSteps: Int,\n    val completedSteps: Int,\n    val stepResults: List<StepResult>,\n    val executionTimeMs: Long = 0\n)\n\ndata class StepResult(\n    val stepNumber: Int,\n    val stepText: String,\n    val success: Boolean,\n    val error: String? = null\n)\n```\n\n### Creating Custom Macros (Future)\n\nCurrently stubbed for V2. Will support:\n- User-created macros\n- Macro sharing (export/import)\n- Conditional logic (if/then/else)\n- Loop support\n- Macro marketplace\n\n---\n\n## Multi-Language Support\n\nCommandManager supports multiple languages through a locale-aware system.\n\n### Supported Locales\n\n- `en-US` - English (United States)\n- `es-ES` - Spanish (Spain)\n- `fr-FR` - French (France)\n- `de-DE` - German (Germany)\n\n### Command Files\n\nLocated in: `src/main/assets/commands/`\n\n```\ncommands/\n en-US/\n    navigation.json\n    editing.json\n    system.json\n es-ES/\n    navigation.json\n    ...\n ...\n```\n\n### JSON Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"locale\": \"en-US\",\n  \"commands\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"nav_back\",\n      \"patterns\": [\"go back\", \"back\", \"navigate back\", \"previous\", \"return\"],\n      \"category\": \"NAVIGATION\",\n      \"description\": \"Navigate back to previous screen\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"nav_home\",\n      \"patterns\": [\"go home\", \"home\", \"home screen\", \"main screen\"],\n      \"category\": \"NAVIGATION\",\n      \"description\": \"Go to home screen\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Adding New Locale\n\n1. **Create locale directory** in `assets/commands/` (e.g., `ja-JP/`)\n\n2. **Create command JSON files** for each category\n\n3. **Translate command patterns** to target language\n\n4. **Test locale loading:**\n\n```kotlin\nval commandManager = CommandManager.getInstance(context)\nval success = commandManager.switchLocale(\"ja-JP\")\n```\n\n### Locale Fallback\n\nIf requested locale not found:\n1. Try language-only match (e.g., `en-US`  `en`)\n2. Fall back to English (`en-US`)\n3. Log warning and continue\n\n---\n\n## Testing\n\n### Test Structure\n\n```\nsrc/test/java/com/augmentalis/commandmanager/\n CommandManagerTest.kt\n CommandRegistryTest.kt\n actions/\n    EditingActionsTest.kt\n    MacroActionsTest.kt\n    CursorActionsTest.kt\n    ... (all action tests)\n cache/\n    CommandCacheTest.kt\n context/\n    CommandContextManagerTest.kt\n    ContextAwareCommandsTest.kt\n dynamic/\n    DynamicCommandRegistryTest.kt\n integration/\n    CommandManagerIntegrationTest.kt\n learning/\n    HybridLearningServiceTest.kt\n ui/\n     CommandViewModelTest.kt\n```\n\n### Running Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests\n./gradlew :CommandManager:test\n\n# Run specific test class\n./gradlew :CommandManager:test --tests EditingActionsTest\n\n# Run with coverage\n./gradlew :CommandManager:jacocoTestReport\n```\n\n### Writing Tests\n\n```kotlin\n@RunWith(AndroidJUnit4::class)\nclass MyActionTest {\n\n    private lateinit var action: MyAction\n    private lateinit var context: Context\n    private lateinit var mockAccessibilityService: AccessibilityService\n\n    @Before\n    fun setUp() {\n        context = InstrumentationRegistry.getInstrumentation().targetContext\n        mockAccessibilityService = mock()\n        action = MyAction(context, mockAccessibilityService)\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun testActionExecution() = runTest {\n        // Arrange\n        val command = Command(\n            id = \"test_command\",\n            text = \"test\",\n            source = CommandSource.VOICE\n        )\n\n        // Act\n        val result = action.execute(command, mockAccessibilityService, context)\n\n        // Assert\n        assertTrue(result.success)\n        assertNotNull(result.response)\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    fun testActionFailure() = runTest {\n        // Test error handling\n [API Reference](#api-reference)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nLocalizationManager handles user preferences and localization settings for VOS4:\n\n- **User Preferences**: Persistent key-value storage\n- **Message Debounce**: Configurable delay for message display\n- **Statistics Display**: Auto-show configuration\n- **Animation Settings**: Language animation toggles\n- **Detail Levels**: User preference for information density\n\n### Key Features\n\n- SQLDelight database (KMP-ready)\n- Flow-based reactive preferences\n- Compose UI integration\n- Type-safe preference keys\n- Default value Select \"Localization & Display\"\n\n---\n\n## Available Settings\n\n| Setting | Options | Default |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| Message Debounce | Instant to Very Slow | Normal (2 sec) |\n| Statistics Auto-Show | On/Off | Off |\n| Language Animation | On/Off | On |\n| Detail Level | Minimal/Standard/Comprehensive | Standard |\n\n---\n\n## Debounce Duration\n\nControls how long messages stay on screen before being replaced.\n\n### Options\n\n| Option | Duration | Best For |\n|--------|----------|----------|\n| **Instant** | No delay | Fast readers, quick interactions |\n| **Fast** | 1 second | Experienced users |\n| **Normal** | 2 seconds | Most users (default) |\n| **Slow** | 3 seconds | Users who prefer more time |\n| **Very Slow** | 5 seconds | Users who need extra reading time |\n\n### How to Change\n\n**Voice:** \"Set message delay to slow\" or \"Make messages slower\"\n\n**Touch:**\n1. Open Localization Settings\n2. Tap \"Message Display Duration\"\n3. Select your preferred option\n\n---\n\n## Statistics Display\n\nControls whether usage statistics are shown automatically.\n\n### Options\n\n| Option | Behavior |\n|--------|----------|\n| **Off** (default) | Statistics only shown when requested |\n| **On** | Statistics shown automatically after commands |\n\n### How to Change\n\n**Voice:** \"Turn on auto statistics\" or \"Show statistics automatically\"\n\n**Touch:**\n1. Open Localization Settings\n2. Toggle \"Auto-Show Statistics\"\n\n---\n\n## Language Animation\n\nControls animations when language or locale changes.\n\n### Options\n\n| Option | Behavior |\n|--------|----------|\n| **On** (default) | Smooth animations on language changes |\n| **Off** | Instant transitions, no animations |\n\n### When to Disable\n\n- If you experience performance issues\n- If you prefer faster transitions\n- For accessibility reasons\n\n### How to Change\n\n**Voice:** \"Disable language animations\" or \"Turn off animations\"\n\n**Touch:**\n1. Open Localization Settings\n2. Toggle \"Language Animation\"\n\n---\n\n## Detail Level\n\nControls how much information is displayed in messages and feedback.\n\n### Options\n\n| Level | Description | Example Feedback |\n|-------|-------------|------------------|\n| **Minimal** | Brief, essential info only | \"Done\" |\n| **Standard** | Balanced detail (default) | \"Navigation: Went back\" |\n| **Comprehensive** | Full details with context | \"Navigation: Successfully navigated back to previous screen (Chrome)\" |\n\n### How to Change\n\n**Voice:** \"Set detail level to comprehensive\" or \"Show more details\"\n\n**Touch:**\n1. Open Localization Settings\n2. Tap \"Detail Level\"\n3. Select your preferred level\n\n---\n\n## Resetting Preferences\n\nTo reset all localization settings to defaults:\n\n### Voice Command\n\nSay: **\"Reset localization settings\"** or **\"Reset display preferences\"**\n\n### Touch\n\n1. Open Localization Settings\n2. Scroll to bottom\n3. Tap \"Reset to Defaults\"\n4. Confirm when prompted\n\n### Default Values\n\nAfter reset:\n- Message Debounce: Normal (2 seconds)\n- Statistics Auto-Show: Off\n- Language Animation: On\n- Detail Level: Standard\n\n---\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Messages Disappear Too Quickly\n\n**Solution:** Increase debounce duration\n- Go to Settings > Localization\n- Change \"Message Display Duration\" to Slow or Very Slow\n\n### Messages Stay Too Long\n\n**Solution:** Decrease debounce duration\n- Go to Settings > Localization\n- Change \"Message Display Duration\" to Fast or Instant\n\n### Animations Causing Lag\n\n**Solution:** Disable animations\n- Go to Settings > Localization\n- Turn off \"Language Animation\"\n\n### Settings Not Saving\n\n**Possible Causes:**\n1. App was force-stopped\n2. Storage permission issues\n3. Database corruption\n\n**Solutions:**\n1. Ensure VOS4 has storage permissions\n2. Try \"Reset to Defaults\"\n3. If persists, clear app data and reconfigure\n\n### Settings Not Applying\n\n**Solution:** Restart VOS4 service\n- Say: \"Restart VoiceOS\" or toggle accessibility service\n\n---\n\n## Voice Command Reference\n\n| Command | Action |\n|---------|--------|\n| \"Open localization settings\" | Opens settings screen |\n| \"Set message delay to [option]\" | Changes debounce duration |\n| \"Turn on/off auto statistics\" | Toggles statistics display |\n| \"Enable/disable animations\" | Toggles language animations |\n| \"Set detail level to [level]\" | Changes detail level |\n| \"Reset localization settings\" | Resets all to defaults |\n\n---\n\n## Related Documentation\n\n- [Developer Manual](./developer-manual.md) - Technical documentation\n- [VOS4 User Guide](../../user-guide/) - General VOS4 help\n\n---\n\n**Last Updated:** 2025-12-01\n**Version:** 2.0.0\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3520,"cache_read_input_tokens":75106,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3520,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1576,"service_tier":"standard"},"context_management":{"applied_edits":[]}},"requestId":"req_011CVhP7Cw9dW31YUUXzbshD","uuid":"315c7c55-787b-4802-8cd3-d0b1adbc0631"}

{"parentUuid":"846f88c5-8538-4846-8ccf-e512ef410b21","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Volumes/M-Drive/Coding/VoiceOS","sessionId":"91c0f8ea-2231-4381-8af9-6d94a841f624","version":"2.0.56","gitBranch":"kmp/main","slug":"peppy-wandering-flask","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# /analyze - Universal Analysis Command\n\n## Usage\n`/analyze [target] [modifiers]`\n\n## Arguments\n| Arg | Required | Description |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| target | No | File, folder, module, or screenshot path (auto-detected) |\n\n## Modifiers\n| Type | Options |\n|------|---------|\n| Analysis | `.code` `.ui` `.workflow` `.docs` |\n| Reasoning | `.cot` `.tot` |\n| Behavior | `.swarm` `.yolo` `.stop` |\n\n## Auto-Detection\n| Input | Type |\n|-------|------|\n| `.kt`, `.java`, `.ts`, `.py`, `.go`, `.rs`, `.swift` | CODE |\n| `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.webp`, `.gif` | UI |\n| `.md` with spec/plan/tasks | WORKFLOW |\n| `.md` other | DOCS |\n| Directory | CODE (scan all) |\n\n---\n\n## Domain Specialist (MANDATORY)\n\n**Spawn specialist before analysis.**\n\n| Domain | Specialist | Level |\n|--------|------------|-------|\n| Memory, performance | Systems | OS-Level |\n| Threading, concurrency | Concurrency | OS-Level |\n| Platform internals | Platform | OS-Level |\n| Security, auth, crypto | Security | PhD-Level |\n| Algorithm complexity | Algorithm | PhD-Level |\n| API, network | Network | Senior |\n| Database, queries | Data | Senior |\n| UI components | UI | Senior |\n\n---\n\n## CoT/ToT Analysis (MANDATORY)\n\n| Method | When | Approach |\n|--------|------|----------|\n| **CoT** | Linear flow | Step-by-step reasoning |\n| **ToT** | Complex/branching | Multi-hypothesis exploration |\n\n**Required Output:**\n```\nANALYSIS:\n- Files read: [list]\n- Call flow: A  B  C\n- Impact scope: [components]\n- Findings: [issues]\n- Method: CoT | ToT\n```\n\n---\n\n## .code - Code Analysis\n\n### 7-Layer Framework\n| Layer | Focus | Priority |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| 1 | Functional Correctness | P0 |\n| 2 | Static Analysis (syntax, types, unused) | P0 |\n| 3 | Runtime Analysis (memory, null, bounds) | P0 |\n| 4 | Dependency Analysis (circular, missing) | P1 |\n| 5 | Error Handling (try/catch, propagation) | P1 |\n| 6 | Architecture (SOLID, patterns, coupling) | P2 |\n| 7 | Performance (complexity, bottlenecks) | P2 |\n\n### Output Format\n```\nCODE ANALYSIS: {target}\n Functional: [PASS/FAIL] - {issues}\n Static: [PASS/FAIL] - {issues}\n Runtime: [PASS/FAIL] - {issues}\n Dependencies: [PASS/FAIL] - {circular deps}\n Error Handling: [PASS/FAIL] - {gaps}\n Architecture: [score/10] - {violations}\n Performance: [score/10] - Universal Analysis Command\n\n## Usage\n`/analyze [target] [modifiers]`\n\n## Arguments\n| Arg | Required | Description |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| target | No | File, folder, module, or screenshot path (auto-detected) |\n\n## Modifiers\n| Type | Options |\n|------|---------|\n| Analysis | `.code` `.ui` `.workflow` `.docs` |\n| Reasoning | `.cot` `.tot` |\n| Behavior | `.swarm` `.yolo` `.stop` |\n\n## Auto-Detection\n| Input | Type |\n|-------|------|\n| `.kt`, `.java`, `.ts`, `.py`, `.go`, `.rs`, `.swift` | CODE |\n| `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.webp`, `.gif` | UI |\n| `.md` with spec/plan/tasks | WORKFLOW |\n| `.md` other | DOCS |\n| Directory | CODE (scan all) |\n\n---\n\n## Domain Specialist (MANDATORY)\n\n**Spawn specialist before analysis.**\n\n| Domain | Specialist | Level |\n|--------|------------|-------|\n| Memory, performance | Systems | OS-Level |\n| Threading, concurrency | Concurrency | OS-Level |\n| Platform internals | Platform | OS-Level |\n| Security, auth, crypto | Security | PhD-Level |\n| Algorithm complexity | Algorithm | PhD-Level |\n| API, network | Network | Senior |\n| Database, queries | Data | Senior |\n| UI components | UI | Senior |\n\n---\n\n## CoT/ToT Analysis (MANDATORY)\n\n| Method | When | Approach |\n|--------|------|----------|\n| **CoT** | Linear flow | Step-by-step reasoning |\n| **ToT** | Complex/branching | Multi-hypothesis exploration |\n\n**Required Output:**\n```\nANALYSIS:\n- Files read: [list]\n- Call flow: A  B  C\n- Impact scope: [components]\n- Findings: [issues]\n- Method: CoT | ToT\n```\n\n---\n\n## .code - Code Analysis\n\n### 7-Layer Framework\n| Layer | Focus | Priority |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| 1 | Functional Correctness | P0 |\n| 2 | Static Analysis (syntax, types, unused) | P0 |\n| 3 | Runtime Analysis (memory, null, bounds) | P0 |\n| 4 | Dependency Analysis (circular, missing) | P1 |\n| 5 | Error Handling (try/catch, propagation) | P1 |\n| 6 | Architecture (SOLID, patterns, coupling) | P2 |\n| 7 | Performance (complexity, bottlenecks) | P2 |\n\n### Output Format\n```\nCODE ANALYSIS: {target}\n Functional: [PASS/FAIL] - {issues}\n Static: [PASS/FAIL] - {issues}\n Runtime: [PASS/FAIL] - {issues}\n Dependencies: [PASS/FAIL] - {circular deps}\n Error Handling: [PASS/FAIL] - {gaps}\n Architecture: [score/10] - {violations}\n Performance: [score/10] -
